4. Rotate List Right by One Position

Problem

Rotate the list to the right by one position.

Example

numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4]

Solution

numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4]

last = numbers[-1]

for i in range(len(numbers) - 1, 0, -1):
    numbers[i] = numbers[i - 1]

numbers[0] = last

print(numbers)

Output

[4, 1, 2, 3]

