10. Split List Into Two Equal Halves

Problem

Split a list into two equal halves.

Example

numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]

Solution

numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]

mid = len(numbers) // 2

first_half = numbers[:mid]
second_half = numbers[mid:]

print(first_half)
print(second_half)

Output

[1, 2, 3]
[4, 5, 6]

